<br>
I think Bendi is a good person from what I know of her.  She's helped out on other Fed raids and generally been friendly and, well, friendly.  I expect she is also a good raid leader.<br>
<br>
I cannot be any more plain than I was in my prior post:  I do not support non-Fed raids with my limited game time.  If a raid is being conducted, and it is open to everyone, Fed and non-Fed, I will not support the raid and I will ask members of Unhomed to do the same.  Each guild has other things they can be doing with their time.  We often choose to use our time going on Fed raids because we believe in The Federation.  We do not believe in random_guild_001.  Rather than blow off the other 101 things we could be doing and back a raid with five random_guild_001's, we will do something specifically Fed-only or do something Unhomed-only.  Its that simple.  Its not a matter of loot (if it were, we'd attend the raid regardless) and its not about pissiness (random_guild_001 is welcome to great loot and great epics, just not specifically on our dime and in the name of our alliance) or about my respect for Bendi, its about policy.<br>
<br>
As respects the actual topic of this thread:  I think that a &quot;Federation Discussion Forum&quot; by its very title and nature is necessarily limited to Federation-related discussions.  In addition, more than one person asked that at least one of the threads be removed from the board.  I like Shey, don't get me wrong, but I don't have a problem limiting &quot;Federation Discussion Forum&quot; to Federation topics. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ubendieq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BendiEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/24/02 2:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> my position</span><hr size=1> This whole thing is political, and I abhor politics. On the other hand, I owe a clear explanation of my position.<br>
<br>
Though, for the record, my raids are merely okay. I'm not a good raid leader, but I do lead raids - which is more than many folks. My raids are getting better, but I definatly lack the flair that a good raid leader brings to the job.<br>
<br>
My own bias - which I freely admit to - is that I am rabidly anti uber. With a passion. I'm into playing for fun, not to increase a random yellow length of pixels, nor to rabidly seek another collection of pixels, with a different name. Uber is mostly an attitude. Its a &quot;mine, mine, mine and to hell with everyone else&quot; attitude. Its a &quot;I'll be level 60, with *everything*, and so will everyone I know, at any cost, and to hell with everyone else&quot; attitude. What folks rarely recognize, is that getting 60 is no accomplishment - its a dead end. If you play long enough, you'll get to 60. Its a given. Its inherent in the game.<br>
<br>
The federation is a coalition of small to medium sized guilds. Its sole purpose is not to do things that individual guilds can't do, but to do things that the lack of &quot;uber&quot; mindset prevents individual guilds from doing. I know that LoLF/LoOF and Dark Legion at least, could, on paper, kill Talendor, or do Chardok royals raid with just guild resources *if* they could mobilize the full guild resources at any one time. If either guild had a true uber mentality among its members, it could mobilize to do those things - pagers would buzz, phones would ring, and folks would converge. Thank GOD that isn't the case. <br>
<br>
However, that &quot;uber mindset&quot; rot is growing within the Federation. And, its been getting stronger for some time. Thats exactly what's reared its head here, and Vigdis's view is dangerously close to it.<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to interfere with how anyone else plays the game. The federation has several raid leaders, you certainly are not going to miss a mediocre mid level leader. This Uber taint is not something I want rubbing off on me. Just as Vigdis doesn't support open raids, I don't support a policy of closed raids. The occasional, rare closed raid is a good thing. As a general policy, it smacks of uber, and I (as an individual) ain't touching that rotten fish with a 12 and a half foot pole. <br>
<br>
I agree with Vigdis on one point - the Fed needs to set a policy. And, I think you would be better off adding two forums, keep this one as an open chat, and have a closed chat. Have a closed raids forum, and an open raids forum. There is a lot of fog around the federation right now. I've tried, several times now, to get some of this fog cleared up, and I've gotten frustrated with the total lack of any feedback.<br>
<br>
My playtime is limited - by definition, everyone's is. I don't want a reputation for elitism and &quot;Uber&quot; to rub off on my reputation by association. My reputation might not be the best, but its mine, and I value it. Guilt by association is nothing I want any part of, or to even be near.<br>
<br>
Thats my position.<br>
<br>
Bendi Witherspoon<br>
Legion of Little Folk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uyarrick40k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yarrick40k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#70DB93>(6/24/02 2:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What has happened to...</span><hr size=1> I'm not a Federation member (used to be..), but I enjoy hanging out with a good majority of the people in it.  I have a lot of respect for many members of this community.<br>
<br>
However, I'm assuming Vigdis' attitude/response isn't indicative of the rest of the Federation?  If it is, since when did the Federation become some sort of &quot;elite club&quot; for a select group of people?  From the Fed rules forum:<br>
<br>
&gt;** The Idea behind the Federation **<br>
&gt;<br>
&gt;The Federation should help to increase the number of Raids &gt;and allow to Raid harder Dungeons and Encounters. Another &gt;point is to meet new people and it should make pick up &gt;groups easier for all.<br>
<br>
<br>
&gt;** Q&amp;A about Raid **<br>
<br>
&gt;Are all Raids Automatically Federation Raids?<br>
&gt;No, each Guild can make Guildintern Raids. Our Guild for &gt;example do Roleplay specific Raids so we raided Oggok for &gt;the Purpose of defeating the world against the evil Ogres. In &gt;such Raids there is no place for Large people :-)<br>
<br>
<br>
So, while I think people should respect Unhomed's/Vigdis' request to not include non-Fed members on their own raid, I think it's completely unjustified for her to almost &quot;make&quot; them not attend Fed raids with non-Fed members led by other guilds.  That seems a little snobbish and stuck up to me, but that's just my opinion.<br>
<br>
Now might be a good time for the Federation to figure out what the &quot;official&quot; policy is on non-Fed members coming on raids (if it's enforced as a whole, or on an individual basis).<br>
<br>
Just my opinion, but thought I should say something.<br>
